{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id7858e80d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s590y"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"590y"},"text":"§ 590y.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization and purpose of investigation, construction, and maintenance of projects; title to projects; limitation on costs","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of stabilizing water supply and thereby rehabilitating farmers on the land and providing opportunities for permanent settlement of farm families, the Secretary of the Interior (hereinafter referred to as “the Secretary”) is authorized to investigate and, upon compliance with the provisions of this subchapter, to construct water conservation and utilization projects in the Great Plains and arid and semiarid areas of the United States, and to operate and maintain each such project in accordance with the provisions of this subchapter; ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That the United States shall retain title to the dams, reservoirs, irrigation, and other project works until Congress otherwise provides: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"And provided further","children":[],"tail":", That expenditures from appropriations made directly pursuant to the authority contained in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s590z–10/1"},"text":"section 590z–10(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":" to meet reimbursable construction costs allocated to irrigation as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s590z–2/b"},"text":"section 590z–2(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall not exceed $2,000,000 for dams and reservoirs in any one project, and that expenditures from appropriations made directly pursuant to the authority contained in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s590z–10/1"},"text":"section 590z–10(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":" to meet costs allocated to flood control by the Secretary after consultation with the Chief of Engineers, Department of the Army, shall not exceed $500,000 on any one project."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id7858e80e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-08-11/ch717/s1"},"text":"Aug. 11, 1939, ch. 717, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1418"},"text":"53 Stat. 1418","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-10-14/ch861"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1940, ch. 861","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/1119"},"text":"54 Stat. 1119","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1942-03-07/ch164"},"text":"Mar. 7, 1942, ch. 164","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/56/142"},"text":"56 Stat. 142","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1943-07-16/ch242/s1"},"text":"July 16, 1943, ch. 242, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/57/566"},"text":"57 Stat. 566","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343"},"text":"July 26, 1947, ch. 343","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 205(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id7858e80f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id7858e810-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id7858e811-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1943—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1943-07-16"},"text":"July 16, 1943","children":[],"tail":", raised amount of expenditures for dams and reservoirs on any one project from $1,000,000 to $2,000,000."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1942—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1942-03-07"},"text":"Mar. 7, 1942","children":[],"tail":", amended last proviso."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1940—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1940-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1940","children":[],"tail":", reenacted section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id7858e812-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id7858e813-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Department of War designated Department of the Army and title of Secretary of War changed to Secretary of the Army by section 205(a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343/tII"},"text":"act July 26, 1947, ch. 343, title II","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":". Section 205(a) of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1947","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by section 53 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/641"},"text":"70A Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":". Section 1 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956","children":[],"tail":", enacted “Title 10, Armed Forces” which in sections 3010 to 3013 continued military Department of the Army under administrative supervision of Secretary of the Army."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id7858e814-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Angostura Project","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-08-09/ch630"},"text":"Act Aug. 9, 1955, ch. 630","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/552"},"text":"69 Stat. 552","children":[],"tail":", provided: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/act/1955-08-09/ch630"},"text":"“That the provisions of sections 41(g), 43, and 51 of the Bankhead-Jones Farm Tenant Act, as amended [sections 1015(g), 1017, and 1025 of Title 7, Agriculture], are hereby extended to apply on the obligations of settlers on the Angostura project in South Dakota developed under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1939-08-11"},"text":"August 11, 1939","children":[],"tail":", as amended [this section].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
